We recommended that the LCE direct the:

BAC and its TWG to:
complete the post-qualification process within the allowable time frame. If the 12-day period proves insufficient, the BAC must promptly request approval from the HoPE for any necessary extension;
scrutinize the contractor’s submitted list of key personnel to be assigned to the contract and thoroughly examine it for any overlapping assignments. In cases where personnel are found to be concurrently assigned to multiple projects during the same period, require the contractor, through a written request, to replace the concerned personnel. Failure to comply should result in the disqualification of the contractor for non-compliance with the technical requirements of the procurement process; and
require the winning bidder to submit a CSHP approved by the DOLE before signing the contract for an infrastructure project, in accordance with Section 37.2 of the Revised IRR of RA 9184.
Municipal Engineer to:
develop and implement a system for the regular updating of project signboards, aligned with the schedule outlined in Section 3 of COA Circular No. 2013-004, to ensure that these accurately reflect the actual progress of infrastructure projects, thereby promoting transparency and reinforcing public accountability;
ensure that photos before, during and after the project implementation, including photos of the project signboards, are attached to the DVs;
implement standardized field inspection checklists and reporting templates to ensure that project signboards comply with the specifications in the POW; and
develop and adopt a uniform costing template or guidelines for the preparation of project signboard estimates, in order to promote consistency and fairness, and to minimize discretion in cost estimation.

We recommended that the LCE direct the Municipal Accountant to:
effect the proposed reclassification entry as follows:
restate the financial statements to reflect the proposed reclassification entry;
conduct a thorough review of the Lapsing Schedule of PPE to identify PPE accounts recorded in lump-sum amounts and lacking specific details such as quantity and unit cost;
retrieve and examine the pertinent documents to determine whether the individual items fall below the capitalization threshold and, if so, prepare the necessary reclassification entry/ies;
hereafter, ensure that all procured PPE items are reflected in the lapsing schedule with complete details to support clear identification and proper classification;
classify the PPE items in the lapsing schedule by account category to facilitate easier reconciliation with the corresponding general ledger accounts;
provide an additional disclosure in the NFS regarding the change in accounting policy, in compliance with Paragraph 34 of IPSAS No. 3; and
delegate the preparation of the PPE schedule and other related tasks to other staff members. If the current manpower is deemed insufficient, request additional personnel from the Human Resource and Management Office.

We recommended that the LCE direct the Municipal Accountant to:
prepare the adjusting entries to recognize the Trust Liability-DRRMF in the Trust Fund books and record the appropriate entries upon reconciliation of the unidentified balance;
immediately facilitate the transfer of cash balances related to unutilized LDRRMF allocations for CYs 2023 and 2024;
provide adequate and accurate disclosures in the NFS regarding the restricted funds of the Cash in Bank-LCCA to ensure that relevant information is available to the intended users of the financial statements; and
develop and implement a strategic allocation of responsibilities among accounting personnel to ensure even distribution of tasks throughout the fiscal year, thereby reducing the year-end workload pressures, minimizing the risk of errors, and enhancing the accuracy and timeliness of financial reporting.

We recommended the LCE direct the Municipal Accountant to:
recognize the RPT/SET Receivables at the beginning of the year based on a certified list from the Municipal Treasurer;
properly apply collections against recorded receivables and recognize the corresponding revenues and inter-LGU liabilities at the time of collection;
facilitate the timely and accurate transfer of RPT and SET shares to the concerned partner LGUs in accordance with allocation guidelines; and
prepare the necessary adjusting journal entries to correct the balances of the affected accounts, as proposed below:

We recommended that the LCE direct the Municipal Accountant to:
discontinue the practice of reclassifying abnormal balances into unrelated accounts to ensure that all pertinent accounts accurately reflect their proper balances to maintain financial transparency and uphold compliance with accounting standards;
prepare the necessary adjusting journal entry to restore the correct balances of the affected accounts, as proposed below:
expedite the reconciliation process of the abnormal amount and prepare the necessary adjusting entries to correct discrepancies and align records with actual transactions;
compile and submit pertinent supporting documents to provide clear justification for adjustments and facilitate transparent financial reporting; and
establish and consistently maintain subsidiary ledgers for all withheld taxes to enhance monitoring, accuracy, and accountability in the tracking of tax obligations.

