We have recommended that the Management:
Require additional payment for the uncollected penalties during the CY 2019. Thereafter, strictly implement the penalty provisions of the current Tax Ordinance, requiring assessment and collection of penalties for delayed payments of business taxes as additional income may be realized to fund the projects to be implemented, as well as to ensure earlier collection of business taxes;
Require the submission of certified copy of Annual Income Tax Return to Business Taxpayers on the second quarter of the year; adjust the business tax and; collect the difference if there are discrepancies between the amount appearing in the ITR and gross sales declared in the business tax application form.

1. We reiterated the following recommendations that:

a.	The Inventory Committee conduct annual physical inventory of all Property, Plant and Equipment of the municipality in order to determine their existence and condition;
b.	The GSO maintain property cards per category of PPE;
c.	The Accounting Unit maintain complete property ledger cards for all PPE owned by the agency;
d.	The Accounting Unit record all PPE additions/acquisitions using the AIR and immediately reflect them to the property ledger cards;
e.	The GSO Designate and Accounting Unit exert effort in reconciling their records from time to time;
f.	The GSO Designate and Accounting Unit effect the proper documentation and immediate disposition of all unserviceable property;
g.	The Accounting unit exert effort in locating or producing the documents to support the legitimacy of the unreconciled PPE account balances and thereafter, strengthen the control over documentation of all financial transactions; and
h.	The Accounting Unit to book the Municipal Building and Slaughterhouse for fair presentation of financial statements.
i.	We have recommended further that representations be made by the Municipality to DPWH in order to be informed on the cost of the building since it was occupied in 2016.

2.1. We have recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:

a.	Municipal Accountant to maintain subsidiary ledgers of all the accounts;
b.	Prepare and submit monthly Bank Reconciliation Statements of all its depository bank accounts; take up reconciling items, and effect the adjustments in the GL/SL to ensure the correct balance of the Cash in Bank accounts;
c.	Exert more time and effort to trace, verify, and reconcile regularly the book balances against the bank records including reconciliation with the cashbook maintained by the Municipal Treasurer; and
d.	Municipal Treasurer to coordinate with the depository banks to ensure prompt delivery of the monthly bank statements with supporting documents to facilitate timely  Reconciliation of the Cash in Bank accounts..

7. We have reiterated our recommendation that Management:

