We have reiterated the following recommendations:
The Local Chief Executive to create inventory committee to conduct physical inventory of all Property, Plant and Equipment of the municipality in order to determine their existence and condition;
The GSO to maintain property cards per category of PPE;
The Accounting unit to maintain complete property ledger cards for all PPE owned by the agency;
The GSO Designate to issue ARE to all property accountable officials and employees and keep copies thereof;
The GSO Designate and Accounting Unit to exert effort in reconciling their records;
The GSO Designate and Accounting unit to effect the proper documentation and immediate disposition of all unserviceable property; and
The Accounting unit to exert effort in locating or producing the documents to support the legitimacy of the unreconciled PPE account balances and thereafter, strengthen the control over documentation of all financial transactions.
The Accounting unit to disclose in their notes the change in accounting estimate due to decrease in residual value and the gross carrying amount of any fully depreciated property, plant and equipment that is still in use.

With the foregoing, we recommended that the Municipal Mayor direct the:
Bids and Awards Committee to prepare and submit the Annual Procurement Plan prior the start of the year based on the Approved Budget of the Municipality;
Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator and Municipal Engineer to submit complete list of all on-going government projects/programs/activities and those that are to be implemented during the year at the beginning of the year;
MPDC and Municipal Engineer to compel the contractors to post the required billboards; and
MPDC and Municipal Engineer to inform the audit team and Supervising Auditor that the appropriate project signboards and/or public notices are already posted.
